";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:20:"It&#039;s amazing...";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:75:"http://indytaxdollars.typepad.com/indy_tax_dollars/2013/08/its-amazing.html";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:75:"http://indytaxdollars.typepad.com/indy_tax_dollars/2013/08/its-amazing.html";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:4:"true";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:235:"...how often we find that we could have used the phrase "here we go again" for the title of our essay. Thursday morning’s paper gives us another blast headed, "Transit debate refueled." Starting on the front page and continuing on...";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Sun, 04 Aug 2013 13:36:02 -0400";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2661:"<p>...how often we find that we could have used the phrase &quot;here we go again&quot; for the title of our essay.&#0160; Thursday morning’s paper gives us another blast headed, &quot;Transit debate refueled.&quot;</p>
<p>Starting on the front page and continuing on pages three and four, it includes a map - of about a quarter page - of the proposal. &#0160;The map pretty well gives us the proposed layout of the <strong>Red Line</strong> - Greenwood to Carmel; the <strong>Blue Line </strong>- East Washington Street to the airport; and the <strong>Green line </strong>- Noblesville to downtown Indianapolis.</p>
<p>Red and Blue are identified as &quot;bus rapid transit&quot; routes, while Green is listed as &quot;either train or buses.&quot; &#0160;Disappointment there.&#0160; We were under the impression that rail usage had been eliminated as a feasible possibility.</p>
<p>We had apparently upset some folks earlier when we referred to a &quot;Stadium-to-Palladium&quot; route.&#0160; It is nice to have our nomenclature verified, in that the northern section of the Red Line runs from downtown Indy to Carmel, ending at City Center.</p>
<p>We have argued in favor of a public transit system which will allow citizens of Indianapolis to be able to get around - and across - town.&#0160; We have insisted that spending history here indicates that particular idea will have a very low priority.</p>
<p>Our fears seem to be justified by two things. &#0160;The very extensive story on Thursday contains this <span style="text-decoration: underline;">one sentence</span> about the proposal from &quot;Indy Connect,&quot; the organization pushing the concept.&#0160; &quot;Its plan also would double the size of IndyGo.&quot;</p>
<p>This then, is followed by a half-page presentation on the back of the Metro section of this morning’s paper (Sunday). &#0160;The first sentence of the text says, &quot;We need your input as we <strong>continue studying the Red, Blue and Green Rapid Transit lines</strong>.&quot;&#0160; (Our emphasis.) </p>
<p>It repeats the original map, with a few unidentified additions, and lists nine locations where public meetings will be held. &#0160;Each of these meetings is identified by color, indicating which of the three proposed lines will be the appropriate subject.&#0160; Are we too cynical in our reading of a line saying &quot;Guided discussions will be held every fifteen minutes&quot; which appears on the map itself?&#0160;</p>
<p>&#0160;We understand the need to stay on topic at such a public meeting. The question is, <strong>&quot;When will the specific topic be the improvement of IndyGo?&quot;</strong></p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Fred McCarthy";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}}}s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";a:1:{s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:3:"rel";s:4:"self";s:4:"href";s:58:"http://indytaxdollars.typepad.com/indy_tax_dollars/rss.xml";s:4:"type";s:19:"application/rss+xml";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}}}}}}}}s:4:"type";i:128;s:7:"headers";a:12:{s:6:"server";s:6:"Apache";s:7:"x-phapp";s:13:"oak-tp-web049";s:11:"x-webserver";s:13:"oak-tp-web049";s:4:"vary";s:6:"cookie";s:13:"last-modified";s:29:"Thu, 15 Aug 2013 17:48:16 GMT";s:10:"keep-alive";s:20:"timeout=300, max=100";s:12:"content-type";s:19:"application/rss+xml";s:14:"content-length";s:5:"21465";s:4:"date";s:29:"Thu, 15 Aug 2013 19:42:33 GMT";s:9:"x-varnish";s:10:"2424484998";s:3:"age";s:1:"0";s:3:"via";s:11:"1.1 varnish";}s:5:"build";s:14:"20130725024141";}